Description: An efficient cross-validated approach for covariance matrix
    estimation, particularly useful in high-dimensional settings. The general
    methodology allows for cross-validation to be used to data-adaptively
    identify the optimal estimator of the covariance matrix from a pre-specified
    set of candidate estimators.
Depends: R (>= 3.6.0)
